splash.splashContent:
Welcome to the inEQUALITY app!


     Spatial analysis of marginalization and deprivation in the 

    City of Toronto

about.aboutContent:
With the help of inEQUALITY app, we strive to provide the highest quality of care and support to individuals who are experiencing financial hardships based on the personal type of need. Through utilizing various functions of our app, you will be able to gain ample information and support on the different types of help and services locations that are provided by the City of Toronto.
Adult educational programs, affordable housing, food banks, shelters, financial services, and employment resources are examples of quality spatial information provided by our app which can help you through the rough patches of your life to achieve a better future.


You can click on the "How to" icon on the top right corner of the page for a brief tutorial on how to use the functions of this app. 


Please make sure that you fill this voluntary survey to help us and the City of Toronto to identify what types of supportive services will be needed in your community

Toronto Neighbourhood Deprivation Index (TNDI)


Since certain communities of interest may not be adequately represented, indicators of inequality and marginalization may be difficult to analyze using conventional administrative data sources. However, the use of area-based, spatially derived indexes can be extremely beneficial in analyzing and solving social and socioeconomic issues.
An example of such indexes is the Toronto Neighbourhood Deprivation Index (TNDI) that has been derived from 9 social indicators and can be simplified into the three categories of residential instability, financial difficulties, and situational vulnerability. The inEQUALITY app with the help of TNDI allows for a better understanding of spatial variability of inequality in the neighbourhoods of Toronto. You can use the "Help Near Me" tool to find services within a predefined distance of your chosen location. You can click on "Find my location"  to allow the application to automatically find your current location, or you can entre your address manually. If you value your privacy and do not prefer to reveal your location, postal codes can also be utilized in this tool. Click on "Set location"  to manually select a location on the map.




The "Filter Services" tool allows you to locate service types based on your needs and limits the visibility of features that are not needed/selected. Select a service type in this tool, and only the service locations that meet this criteria will be visible on the map. 




The "Legend" helps you to differentiate between types of service locations and the values of TNDI on the map.




You can view the list of operational layers and toggle them on and off by using the "Layer List" tool.
